    Class
    Description
    DoesNotExist
    Type constraint that is used to verify whether an object already exists in the system with unique properties matching those used in a DTO being used to create a new object or update an existing object.
    ValidDateRange
    Constraint that is used to verify the date represented by the Optional<String> identified by firstDatePropertyName occurs before or on the same date as the Optional<String> identified by secondDatePropertyName.
    ValidDateString
    Field constraint that verifies that if the Optional contains a value then it is a valid date string in DateTimeFormatter.ISO_LOCAL_DATE format.
